cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the state of database research and recommends areas for further focus, indicating that it is likely to belong to the cs.DB (Database) sub-category. The recommendations include integration of text, data, code, and streams, which suggests a connection to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. The recommendation for reasoning about uncertain data suggests a connection to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The recommendation for information privacy suggests a connection to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Finally, the recommendation for unsupervised data mining for interesting correlations suggests a connection to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
